I would like to seek clarification regarding the current promotion of 15% discount storewide for Gold members. Yesterday @ Paragon I was charged the full price for a Grande cup of Hot Chocolate. I realised the overcharge last night and came down to the cafe this afternoon. The manager was on leave. I spoke to a staff. He asserted that it was because I failed to flash the notification email. How can this be? My topped-up account in my mobile app was used for the payment. I am an ultra regular customer @ Paragon Starbucks. I also made a purchase the day before and the discount was deducted automatically from the bill without me having to flash the notification email. Starbucks, I would appreciate if you could comment on this dichotom.

I have a nicely brewed before me a cup of Sumatra from Jurong Point Starbuck Reserve. My coffee has to be taken away because all the seats at the Starbuck Reserve counter are taken by non-reserve customers. In Japan, I have a good experience sitting at the reserved coffee counter to enjoy a specially chosen type of coffee brewed by the barrister. The reserved coffee counter are specially reserved for this special experience and the barristers will bother to explain to those non-reserved coffee customers, not to occupy this reserved area. It would be nice if Singapore Starbuck barristers can consider practise this. Nevertheless, thumb up for the Singapore Starbuck to compliment my drink with a small bite. It is a really good gesture and thoughtfulness showed. I enjoy my Sumatra. :-)

I wouldn't mind topping up a bit to get the peppermint syrup but a peppermint mocha is over a dollar more. A regular mocha also costs more than a regular latte.
